Joan Ellis Beglinger has been a professional nurse since 1975. Her clinical practice included 10 years in critical care, 5 of those as a Clinical Nurse Specialist. Joan has been a health care executive in acute care for 28 years, most recently in the position of Vice President for Patient Care/ Chief Nursing Officer at St. Mary's Hospital in Madison, WI for 22 years. She is currently practicing independently, assisting colleagues in the development of professional practice environments that will position nurses for leadership in the changing health care environment.

Joan is known for her visionary leadership and ability to translate complex concepts into effective operations. Her areas of responsibility have consistently produced exceptional clinical outcomes, high patient satisfaction, employee and physician engagement and operational excellence. Joan spent her career building expertise in transforming the professional practice environment from traditional hierarchy to shared decision making through shared governance. Under her leadership, the St. Mary's Nursing Organization achieved international prominence and the prestigious designation as a Magnet organization since 2002. 

Joan has a Bachelor of Science in Nursing, a Master of Science in Nursing and a Master of Business Administration. She completed a Fellowship for Nurse Executives at the Wharton School of Business and is a Fellow in the American College of Health Care Executives and a Fellow in the American Academy of Nursing. Professional memberships include the American Nurses Association, American Organization of Nurse Executives, Sigma Theta Tau, WBL and the American College of Health Care Executives. 

Joan has spoken extensively nationally and internationally. Her many publications have focused on the development of an organizational culture that supports clinical excellence. She is the author of a department in the Journal of Nursing Administration (JONA) "Spotlight on Transitions".
Trinity Health colleague trained in Just Culture during 4-day course with John Westfall.
